restaurants.name: Benihana
restaurants.description: Talented chefs create sumptuous Teppanyaki dishes with dazzling theatrical cooking displays, promising unforgettable “eatertainment” at every table. Alternatively select from an à la carte menu of hand crafted sushi, sashimi and signature rolls.

restaurants.name: Sirimahannop
restaurants.description: Sirimahannop in Bangkok is ready to transport guests back to an enchanting bygone era of Thai heritage with timeless and elegant decor, historic photographs and everyday utensils that vividly showcase life of the old glorious days. Permanently docked at Asiatique The Riverfront, the popular retail and lifestyle complex by the Chao Phraya River, this classical three-masted vessel invites passengers to step into a vibrant world of mixology and gastronomy, with original beverages infused with native woods and tropical fruits, specialist rum cocktails, craft beers, fine wines, premium spirits, and a mouth-watering menu that showcases fresh local seafood and tapas-style plates.

Head to the lounge, deck or stunning rooftop for sensual beats by Music Director Scotty B and worldly cocktails by award-winning mixologist team.

restaurants.name: Penthouse Bar + Grill
restaurants.description: Penthouse Bar + Grill is an award winning destination that offers six exceptional drinking and dining venues above the Bangkok city. At Level 34, The Grill combines the atmosphere of a classic Manhattan steakhouse with a contemporary twist where Chef de Cuisine Dominic Hong ensures that every quality item from land or sea is cooked to perfection. For something a little different, the Chef's Table offers set course menus for a bespoke dining experience in privacy and comfort. At The Cocktail Bar on level 35, watch head bartender Khun Sabine mix classic cocktails and signature creations as you enjoy live entertainment lineups. Sit at the bar and soak up the vibes or celebrate private moments at The Mezzanine. For a more intimate setting The Whisky Room offers classic jazz to accompany special whisky flights and an impressive selection of 160 labels. On Level 36 the Rooftop Bar is the place to unwind with a sunset Prosecco and an equally sparkling view of the Bangkok skyline.

restaurants.name: New York Steakhouse - at the JW Marriott Hotel Bangkok
restaurants.description: The New York Steakhouse at the JW Marriott Bangkok provides the prefect venue for a special meal. This restaurant,located on the hotels' second floor mezzanine, represents the best of the great American steakhouses.The finest fresh chilled, USDA certified, grain fed, Angus beef is served. Aged to perfection, it is cooked precisely to order. Different cuts and types of Prime beef from around the world with your choice of sauces and sides are featured. Try the Australian Wagyu Tomahawk Steak for two.Traditional appetizers like Clam Chowder, Shrimp Cocktail, House-smoked Salmon and Caesar Salad are popular starters. Dessert vary from Baked Bomb Alaska and New York Cheesecake. There is also a selection of fresh seafood delicacies, as well as some traditional non beef dishes. The wine list is massive and impressive; a full range of cocktails is offered, great Martinis.Opening Hours: 18:00 - 22:30 Reservations: Highly recommended Dress Code: Smart casual (no slipper).
restaurants.address: 4 Sukhumvit Road, Soi 2 JW Marriott Hotel Bangkok, Bangkok 10110 Thailand

restaurants.name: The Silk Road
restaurants.description: Journey down the Silk Road and experience authentic Cantonese specialties. Dine on a dim sum lunch; a pure expression of the Chinese tea and snack tradition, enhanced by decades of refinement. The a la carte menu offers a variety of Cantonese cuisine for lunch and dinner. The Silk Road offers five private dining rooms.
restaurants.address: 61 Witthayu Road The Athenee Hotel, Bangkok 10330 Thailand

restaurants.name: Red Bean Restaurant
restaurants.description: Superb local flavors underpin the foundation of Red Bean’s casual fine dining. Modern and innovative Vietnamese cuisine is demonstrated through menus inspired by classic Quang Nam province recipes, Hoi An specials as well as many of Vietnam’s iconic dishes. At Red Bean we stay true to the roots of authentic and traditional cuisine underpinned by the five elements of metal, earth, wood, fire and water. Red Bean is an airy, simply styled space. It plays to the natural setting outside drawing one’s eye through the Asian paneled windows to the courtyard and surrounding tropical gardens beyond. Note: during holiday periods such as Christmas, New Year, Tet Lunar New Year we will have selected set special menus and we recommend booking a table in advance.
